commit.message: fix #125: parsing of regex rules in peg syntaxes

Fix PEG parsers' "comment" rule

The problem with the previous version was that if there is no text after
the '//', regular whitespace processing kicked in and the regexp was
applied to the next non-empty line.

The effect of this was that the next line gets commented off
unconditionally, which is kindof not what you want.

fix CSV example

importlib.metadata is import Python csv module which interfere with this
example. This changes the name of the module to `csvlang.py`
fix: bring CI config from the master branch
fix: temporary disable a test for this release
fix: improve fix for '\n' in matches failure report
tests: extend tests for '\n' in match failure messages

Error reporting: print newline characters escaped

Potentially closes: https://github.com/textX/textX/issues/397
